column2: WITH event_log AS ( SELECT id, activity, timestamp, resource, cost, idcase, ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY idcase ORDER BY timestamp) AS row_num FROM event_log ) SELECT el1.idcase, el1.activity AS final_activity, el1.timestamp - el2.timestamp AS time_diff FROM event_log el1 JOIN event_log el2 ON el1.idcase = el2.idcase AND el1.row_num = 1 AND el2.row_num = (SELECT MAX(row_num) FROM event_log WHERE idcase = el1.idcase AND activity IN ('end trip', 'declaration rejected by employee', 'payment handled')) WHERE el1.activity IN ('end trip', 'declaration rejected by employee', 'payment handled');
column3: select p.idcase, strftime('%s', p.timestamp) - strftime('%s', e.start_time) as 'End trip', strftime('%s', x.timestamp) - strftime('%s', e.start_time) as 'Declaration rejected by employee', strftime('%s', y.timestamp) - strftime('%s', e.start_time) as 'Payment handled', f.activity from event_log p inner join (select MIN(timestamp) as start_time, idcase FROM event_log GROUP by idcase) e on e.idcase = p.idcase and p.activity = 'End trip' left join event_log x on x.idcase=e.idcase and x.activity = 'Declaration rejected by employee'  left join event_log y on y.idcase=e.idcase and y.activity = 'Payment handled' inner join (select MAX(timestamp) as end_time, activity, idcase FROM event_log WHERE activity='End trip' or activity= 'Declaration rejected by employee' or activity='Payment handled' GROUP by idcase) f on f.idcase=e.idcase

column2: WITH -- Find the first event of each case first_event AS ( SELECT idcase, MIN(timestamp) AS start_time FROM event_log GROUP BY idcase ), -- Find the end event of each case (end trip, declaration rejected, or payment handled) end_event AS ( SELECT idcase, timestamp AS end_time, activity FROM event_log WHERE activity IN ('end trip', 'declaration rejected by employee', 'payment handled') ), -- Join the two tables to find the time interval for each case time_intervals AS ( SELECT fe.idcase, fe.start_time, ee.end_time, DATEDIFF(ee.end_time, fe.start_time) AS time_interval FROM first_event fe JOIN end_event ee ON fe.idcase = ee.idcase ) -- Finally, select the desired columns SELECT ti.idcase, ti.start_time, ti.end_time, ti.time_interval FROM time_intervals ti ORDER BY ti.idcase;

column2: WITH -- Find the first event of each case first_event AS ( SELECT idcase, MIN(timestamp) AS first_timestamp FROM event_log GROUP BY idcase ), -- Find the end event of each case end_event AS ( SELECT idcase, CASE WHEN activity = 'end trip' THEN timestamp WHEN activity = 'declaration rejected by employee' THEN timestamp WHEN activity = 'payment handled' THEN timestamp ELSE NULL END AS end_timestamp FROM event_log ) SELECT fe.idcase, fe.first_timestamp, ee.end_timestamp, TIMESTAMPDIFF(SECOND, fe.first_timestamp, ee.end_timestamp) AS time_taken FROM first_event fe JOIN end_event ee ON fe.idcase = ee.idcase WHERE ee.end_timestamp IS NOT NULL;

column2: SELECT CASE WHEN "resource" LIKE '%employee%' THEN 'Employee' WHEN "resource" LIKE '%supervisor%' THEN 'Supervisor' WHEN "resource" LIKE '%administration%' THEN 'Administration' WHEN "resource" LIKE '%pre-approver%' THEN 'Pre-Approver' WHEN "resource" LIKE '%budget owner%' THEN 'Budget Owner' WHEN "resource" LIKE '%director%' THEN 'Director' ELSE 'Unknown' END AS "Group", COUNT(*) AS "Number of Cases" FROM "event_log" GROUP BY CASE WHEN "resource" LIKE '%employee%' THEN 'Employee' WHEN "resource" LIKE '%supervisor%' THEN 'Supervisor' WHEN "resource" LIKE '%administration%' THEN 'Administration' WHEN "resource" LIKE '%pre-approver%' THEN 'Pre-Approver' WHEN "resource" LIKE '%budget owner%' THEN 'Budget Owner' WHEN "resource" LIKE '%director%' THEN 'Director' ELSE 'Unknown' END ORDER BY "Number of Cases" DESC;
column3: select count(DISTINCT idcase), 'employee' as grupo from event_log WHERE activity like '%employee%'  UNION select count(DISTINCT idcase), 'supervisor' as grupo from event_log WHERE activity like '%supervisor%'  UNION select count(DISTINCT idcase), 'administration' as grupo from event_log WHERE activity like '%administration%'  UNION select count(DISTINCT idcase), 'pre-approver' as grupo from event_log WHERE activity like '%pre-approver%'  UNION select count(DISTINCT idcase), 'budget owner' as grupo from event_log WHERE activity like '%budget owner%'  UNION select count(DISTINCT idcase), 'director' as grupo from event_log WHERE activity like '%director%'

column2: SELECT employee_groups.employee AS "Employee", COUNT(*) AS "Number of cases" FROM event_log JOIN employee_groups ON event_log.idcase = employee_groups.employee OR event_log.idcase = employee_groups.supervisor OR event_log.idcase = employee_groups.administration OR event_log.idcase = employee_groups.pre_approver OR event_log.idcase = employee_groups.budget_owner OR event_log.idcase = employee_groups.supervisor OR event_log.idcase = employee_groups.director GROUP BY employee_groups.employee UNION ALL SELECT supervisor AS "Supervisor", COUNT(*) AS "Number of cases" FROM event_log JOIN employee_groups ON event_log.idcase = employee_groups.supervisor GROUP BY supervisor UNION ALL SELECT administration AS "Administration", COUNT(*) AS "Number of cases" FROM event_log JOIN employee_groups ON event_log.idcase = employee_groups.administration GROUP BY administration UNION ALL SELECT pre_approver AS "Pre-Approver", COUNT(*) AS "Number of cases" FROM event_log JOIN employee_groups ON event_log.idcase = employee_groups.pre_approver GROUP BY pre_approver UNION ALL SELECT budget_owner AS "Budget Owner", COUNT(*) AS "Number of cases" FROM event_log JOIN employee_groups ON event_log.idcase = employee_groups.budget_owner GROUP BY budget_owner UNION ALL SELECT supervisor AS "Supervisor", COUNT(*) AS "Number of cases" FROM event_log JOIN employee_groups ON event_log.idcase = employee_groups.supervisor GROUP BY supervisor UNION ALL SELECT director AS "Director", COUNT(*) AS "Number of cases" FROM event_log JOIN employee_groups ON event_log.idcase = employee_groups.director GROUP BY director;

column2: SELECT COUNT(*) AS total_cases, (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM event_log WHERE activity LIKE '%employee%' OR activity LIKE '%supervisor%' OR activity LIKE '%administration%' OR activity LIKE '%pre-approver%' OR activity LIKE '%budget owner%' OR activity LIKE '%supervisor%' OR activity LIKE '%director%') AS employee_related_cases, (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM event_log WHERE activity LIKE '%supervisor%' OR activity LIKE '%director%') AS supervisor_related_cases, (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM event_log WHERE activity LIKE '%administration%' OR activity LIKE '%director%') AS administration_related_cases, (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM event_log WHERE activity LIKE '%pre-approver%' OR activity LIKE '%budget owner%' OR activity LIKE '%supervisor%' OR activity LIKE '%director%') AS pre_approver_related_cases, (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM event_log WHERE activity LIKE '%budget owner%' OR activity LIKE '%director%') AS budget_owner_related_cases FROM event_log GROUP BY 1;
